# Live Feed / Notification System

A fully functional notification system for CampusConnect where backend modules trigger notifications to targeted users, and the Dashboard's live feed panel polls for new notifications every 15 seconds using short polling.

## Architecture Overview

- **MongoDB** stores all notifications in a `Notification` collection (already connected)
- **Short polling**: Frontend polls `GET /api/notifications` every 15 seconds
- Notifications are targeted:
  - **Personal** (`recipientId` = specific user's Postgres `users_id`)
  - **Broadcast** (`recipientId` = `"all"` — ALL users see these)
- A notification helper `createNotification(type, message, recipientId, metadata)` is used inside all existing controllers

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend – Notification Infrastructure

#### [NEW] `notification.model.js` → `Backend/models/Notification.js`
Mongoose schema:
```
{ type, title, message, recipientId (userId string or "all"), isRead (default false), metadata {}, createdAt }
```

#### [MODIFY] [notification.controller.js](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/dp%20project%20work/CampusConnect/Backend/controllers/notification.controller.js) → [Backend/controllers/notification.controller.js](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/dp%20project%20work/CampusConnect/Backend/controllers/notification.controller.js)
- `getMyNotifications(req, res)` — returns last 50 notifications for `req.verifiedUser.user_id` OR `recipientId = "all"`, sorted by `createdAt desc`
- `markAsRead(req, res)` — marks a single notification read (patch `notificationId`)
- `markAllRead(req, res)` — marks all user's notifications as read

#### [MODIFY] [notification.routes.js](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/dp%20project%20work/CampusConnect/Backend/routes/notification.routes.js) → [Backend/routes/notification.routes.js](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/dp%20project%20work/CampusConnect/Backend/routes/notification.routes.js)
```
GET    /api/notifications          → getMyNotifications  (verifyToken)
PATCH  /api/notifications/:id/read → markAsRead          (verifyToken)
PATCH  /api/notifications/read-all → markAllRead         (verifyToken)
```

#### [NEW] `Backend/utils/notificationHelper.js`
A shared helper used by all controllers:
```js
createNotification(type, title, message, recipientId, metadata)
```
Imports the Notification model and inserts to MongoDB.

